<p style="font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 20px;">
    Week 2 of the Bot vs Bot competition was supposed to be where things got interesting. It got interesting faster than anyone expected.
</p>

<p>On the morning of February 28, BTC sat at <strong>$63,462 — down 6.6% in a single day</strong>. The Fear & Greed Index had hit 11: Extreme Fear, the third consecutive reading at that level. Overnight news of US-Israel military strikes on Iran had already rattled markets; a week of hot macro data and Nvidia earnings pressure did the rest. BTC had fallen from ~$68K to $63K in under a week, invalidating the double-bottom thesis traders had been watching.</p>

<p>This was the harshest market environment our two AI bots had faced since launch. Week 1 was quiet — gates fired, no entries, no losses. Week 2 was different.</p>

